><li><span id="ref35">Abd-Alrazaq A, AlSaad R, Alhuwail D,  et al. Large language models in medical education: opportunities, challenges, and future directions. JMIR Med Educ.  Jun 1, 2023;9:e48291. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.2196/48291">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=37261894&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref36">Wu Y, Zheng Y, Feng B, Yang Y, Kang K, Zhao A. Embracing ChatGPT for medical education: exploring its impact on doctors and medical students. JMIR Med Educ.  Apr 10, 2024;10:e52483. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.2196/52483">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=38598263&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref37">Xu T, Weng H, Liu F,  et al. Current status of ChatGPT use in medical education: potentials, challenges, and strategies. J Med Internet Res.  Aug 28, 2024;26:e57896. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.2196/57896">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=39196640&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref38">Zhui L, Fenghe L, Xuehu W, Qining F, Wei R. Ethical considerations and fundamental principles of large language models in medical education: viewpoint. J Med Internet Res.  Aug 1, 2024;26:e60083. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.2196/60083">CrossRef</a>] [<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=38971715&amp;dopt=Abstract" target="_blank">Medline</a>]</span></li><li><span id="ref39">Buchholz MB. Patterns of empathy as embodied practice in clinical conversation-a musical dimension. Front Psychol.   2014;5:349. [<a target="_blank" href="https://dx.doi.org/10.3389/fpsyg.2014.00349">CrossRef</a>]